- By Authors - In this case a meaningful evaluation of
the partial cross section to the isomer 96-m-Tc with
t1/2=51.5 min was not possible because of the very
uncertain gamma-intensities in the weak B+/EC decay of
this isomer. Qualitatively, however, the data indicate
that the partial cross section to the isomer dominates
the total (p,gamma) rate of 95-Mo by far.
